# DGX sync reminder (after code changes)

Whenever you **create, edit, or delete** files under this repo, **apply scp sync yourself** after the edit (user permission). **Never** run git push/pull/fetch/upstream unless the user explicitly asks.

## Agent behavior (DGX)

1. **Do the work on DGX** (edit, prune, `npm install`, restart API, etc.).
2. **Do not** run `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, or merge `upstream` unless the user explicitly asks.
3. **After DGX-owned changes** — run automatically when Surface SSH works:
   ```bash
   cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio
   bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete
   ```
   Use full `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh` only for a **full** resync (first clone, large drift, or when incremental finds nothing but files are missing).
   Use `--include-src` only when `src/` was edited on DGX (lock first per sync rules):
   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete
   ```
   After milestones, also push agent context:
   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context --retry-until-complete
   bash scripts/sync-sessionmem-team.sh
   ```
4. **After Surface → DGX sync** (PC pushed new scripts/docs) — run:
   ```bash
   bash scripts/ensure-dgx-sync-ready.sh
   ```
5. **Do not** nag about sync if you already ran it. Only report if sync **failed**.
6. **Pitch Deck** — after edits under `Pitch Deck/`, run `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` (prune runs automatically when Pitch Deck paths changed). Never `scp -r "Pitch Deck"` to Surface. See `.cursor/rules/pitch-deck-sync-protected.mdc`. **Never** tell the user to run sync — you run it.

## Incremental sync (DGX side — your assignment)

| Script | When to run on DGX |
|--------|-------------------|
| `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` | **Default after every edit** — git-changed DGX-owned files only |
| `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh` | Full push of all DGX-owned paths (slow; use when incremental is insufficient) |
| `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete` | DGX edited `src/` — locks, pushes changed `src/` files only |
| `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context --retry-until-complete` | Push changed `memory-bank/`, `graphify-out/` |

**Mirror on Surface:** PC uses `.\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete` for the same pattern in the opposite direction.

**Shared library:** `scripts/sync-changes-lib.sh` (sourced by `sync-changes-to-pc.sh`; do not run directly).

**Do not pipe** sync output through `head` / `Select-Object -First` — it can stall `scp`.

## Ownership (which script)

| Changed files | Source of truth | Run on **DGX** |
| ------------- | --------------- | -------------- |
| `src/`, app scripts (`dgx-rehydrate-*.py`, etc.), roadmaps | PC | *(Surface runs `sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1`)* |
| Pitch Deck, README, package.json, docs | DGX | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` |
| `sync-*.ps1`, `sync-changes-*`, `sync-to-pc.sh`, prune/ensure scripts | DGX maintains copies; PC may author | Push from whichever machine edited them |

**Important:** Surface `sync-from-dgx.ps1` does **not** copy `src/` or roadmaps. If you edited `src/` on **DGX**, push before the user can test in the browser:

```bash
cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio
bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete
bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context --retry-until-complete
bash scripts/sync-sessionmem-team.sh
```

Requires OpenSSH on Surface (port 22). Surface rule: `.cursor/rules/surface-sync-reminder.mdc`.

## Scripts (bash, from DGX repo root)

```bash
# Preferred — changed DGX-owned files only
bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete

# Full DGX-owned push
bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh

# After PC pushed sync workflow updates
bash scripts/ensure-dgx-sync-ready.sh
```

Surface pulls the same files with:

```powershell
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1 -Remote
```

## Backend (`3DAIGC-API`)

API changes on DGX take effect after restart on Spark (`:7842`). No PC sync
script — frontend reaches API via `VITE_API_ENDPOINT=/__dev_dgx_proxy` →
`http://10.0.0.158:7842`.

Surface agent rule (local PC): `.cursor/rules/surface-sync-reminder.mdc`

## Equal role on DGX

DGX agent has the **same execute permissions** as Surface: edit files, run `sync-changes-to-pc.sh` automatically after edits, SSH to Surface when needed. Never offer options — do it or report a blocker.
